 pain from the serpent and then from the Atmah Cyane.  Arahuta's eyes looked deep into Alti and suddenly the ground began to rumble around all of them.  Alti stood up, looked at the ground and then to Arahuta. &quot;What a cheap magicians trick!&quot;  As the ground rumbled the sky turned dark as a sudden night fell.  The stars began to show bright and then began to move in a spiral.  Arahuta kept her eyes looking into Alti and said nothing.  Then like a tornado falling from the sky, the stars moved in a twisting pattern landed down around Alti.  The  air around the women spun around the stars that now formed a twister. Alti put her hands down as if trying to get her powers to hold her to the ground.  Ara looked calmly into Alti's eyes and spoke.::: Go in peace.<br>
